ms—offers a unique testing ground for current approaches in film studies and affect studies.Attention to Huppert’s performances can reframe recent discussions on the social and cultural dimensions of emotion and normativity through a compelling paradox: her roles tend to express grandiose and overwhelming conditions central to debates in the humanities—negativity, dispossession, trauma—but through elusive and at times resistant or diminutive forms of expression: what J. Hoberman once called her genius  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Acting & Auditioning.2bisacsh1 aCortez, Iggy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCortez, Iggy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFleishman, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleishman, Ian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKoepnick, Lutz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLübecker, Nikolaj, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRedrobe, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlumpf, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStanford, Henrietta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWheatley, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLE